      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis measurements performed per ASTM F1841-97 modified protocol in temperature-controlled environment (37 ± 0.5 °C). Bovine blood with hematocrit 30 ± 1% used as per FDA hemolysis guidance. Five flow-speed operating points bracket the CPB clinical envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Boundary conditions in CFD matched to measured inlet/outlet pressures within ± 2 mmHg.",
