      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is NIH and derived RH index, directly linked to the regulatory decision criterion. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) corroborate hemolysis mechanism. Clinical relevance established by mapping NIH to plasma free hemoglobin concentration per published correlation (Giersiepen et al.). QoIs align with FDA hemolysis guidance document (2017).",
