      "rationale": "Three independent blood batches used across five operating points with triplicate runs per point (n=45 total measurements). Batch-to-batch hematocrit variability < 1.5%; inter-run CV for NIH < 6%. Pump hardware from single manufacturing lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to nominal geometry. Sample size adequate to resolve experimental uncertainty at 95% confidence per power analysis.",
