  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and each achieves its required level for MRL 2. Software QA, code verification, discretization error, model form, model inputs, validation relevance, and output comparison each achieve Gradation 3, exceeding the MRL 2 requirement. The remaining six factors (test conditions, QoI relevance, solver error, use error, test samples, input equivalency) achieve Gradation 2, meeting the requirement exactly. The primary quantity of interest (NIH/RH) is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1). The worst-case RH across all geometric variants and UQ ensemble is 0.87, satisfying the acceptance criterion with margin. Global sensitivity analysis identifies dominant uncertainty contributors; their combined effect is bounded within the 8.3% mean prediction error. The validation dataset spans the full CPB clinical operating envelope on the same device geometry as the COU. Independent peer review and documented QMS provide assurance against use error. On the basis of the structured evidence and the complete credibility factor assessment, the model is accepted for its intended use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
